<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/164422-i-know-that-this-is-a-respected-classic">I know that this is a respected classic, but I didn&#39;t find it very enjoyable to read. It lacked a certain something. Am I the only one who felt this way?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_164422'><a id="like_count_community_question_164422" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/164422?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">63 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F8909.The_War_of_the_Worlds">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/164422-i-know-that-this-is-a-respected-classic">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/164422-i-know-that-this-is-a-respected-classic">See all 28 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/46623410-amazingbollweevil"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/46623410-amazingbollweevil">Amazingbollweevil</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">When I read people complain that this book is .... uh, lacking or something, I can&apos;t help but shake my head in disappointment. The story is one of sur<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">When I read people complain that this book is .... uh, lacking or something, I can't help but shake my head in disappointment. The story is one of survival in the face of overwhelming opposition. The protagonist is totally helpless as he watches his civilization be destroyed by monstrous invaders. He's no hero trying to save the day, but an everyman just trying to get by. This story is now an archetype, having inspired countless other novels and movies and television episodes. Because you have seen these later stories, you already know how this novel will go, so it's no wonder there are no surprises. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

<div class='flagAnswer'>
<a class="right flag" rel="nofollow" id="flag_link411434" title="Flag this answer as inappropriate." href="/flagged/new?resource_id=411434&amp;resource_type=CommunityAnswer&amp;return_url=%2Fquestions%2F164422-i-know-that-this-is-a-respected-classic%2Fanswers%2F411434-when-i-read-people">flag</a>
</div>
<ul class='communityQAFooter answerFooter'>
</ul>

</div>
